&lt;p&gt;As an Account Director at SixSpeed, you will take a leadership role in shaping the success of the agency, managing high-profile client relationships, and driving innovation within the creative and strategic deliverables.&amp;nbsp; As the visionary and results-driven leader, with a passion for client relationships, strategic direction, and team management, you will be given the transformative opportunity to shape the future of the agency and grow our clients’ businesses. Being a strong collaborator is essential, as we treat our clients as an extension of SixSpeed and our internal team members as family. We are looking for a confident, yet humble, leader to help us take one of our largest, longest standing clients to the next level.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TASK AT HAND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze any project’s performance and provide clients with strategic insights and recommendations for improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new business opportunities and contribute to business development efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay at the forefront of industry trends and evolving advertising and marketing strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide exceptional customer service and act as the primary point of senior level contact for key clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver influential client presentations and proposals, driving growth and client satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee annual account panning and financials for each client portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain credibility and leadership with the client through strategic thinking and the use of sound judgment when solving problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead strategic planning and thought leadership with internal team and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and nurture strong, long-term client relationships by understanding their goals, objectives, and expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with clients to develop high-level advertising and marketing strategies and oversee their execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the successful delivery of complex integrated advertising projects, exceeding client expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a team of Account Supervisors, Account Executives, and Coordinators, guiding their professional growth and ensuring team success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide leadership/motivation and convey the vision and values of SixSpeed Account Management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of account management / client management experience within an agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in strategic communications, marketing, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and negotiation skills, with the ability to inspire and influence teams and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking, project management, and organizational abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of the advertising and marketing industry, emerging trends, and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding problem-solving skills, with a strong analytical and data-driven approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated creativity in developing innovative solutions to client challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of consistently meeting or exceeding sales and performance targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven leadership with multiple client relationships and internal team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent ability to develop team members skills and leads by example&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exemplifies the ability to teach and lead team members to grow, develop, present, and sell in strategic work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to grow, develop and teach marketing acumen to internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent financial acumen and ability to teach and lead team members to manage account fo

&lt;p&gt;SixSpeed is looking for an Art Director with 2-5 years of art direction experience to join our team who will generate ideas, generate concepts and guide teams to develop the visual look for all brand communications. Not limited to just the consideration of visuals, we require an emotionally intelligent storyteller who thoughtfully creates structure and emphasis with words, images and sounds to not just connect with people, but drive them to act. We’ll expect you to actively collaborate, inspire and guide partners and teams in the creation and development of exciting new ideas and work that make adventurous brands impossible to imitate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TASK AT HAND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the visual look of a project or campaign ensuring the work is consistent, distinct, appropriate, engaging and that communication is clear&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with copywriters to generate a volume of ideas and concepts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the collaborative visual development of projects and campaigns by guiding teams, producers and partners with a clear direction from start to finish&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Concept and execute across all mediums with attention to detail and visual precision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains awareness of trends in culture and industry producing new thinking and looks for clients and the agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of shot list, treatment and vision for capture and present the vision and plan with producers and account partners to client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel to direct photo and video shoots ensuring the vision is met and the shotlist is captured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selection of image assets post-capture providing retouch direction to partners and presenting for approval with account to clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and understand client&#39;s needs, brand, products, audience and competition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find, recommend and select vendor partners (e.g. photographers, retouchers, video production houses, editors, sound mixers and illustrators, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build positive working relationships with all team members, vendors and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, timely, and helpful feedback with partners to improve creative output and processes keeping work on budget and schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate vision, ideas and concepts to peers and clients—listening and reacting to feedback appropriately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A visual creative with 2-5 years in a brand advertising or marketing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about powersports and adventure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owner of a strong portfolio demonstrating an ability to craft and build creative campaigns driven by audience insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite (Primarily: Illustrator, Photoshop and InDesign)(Secondarily: Lightroom, Bridge and Premiere)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A critical thinker, detail-oriented, passionate, motivated, ambitious and resourceful professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized, open-minded, and capable of delivering tangible results in a fast-paced and creative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positive, empathetic, collaborative and trustworthy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have eyes and ears for spotting creative opportunity—both large and small&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable of photography and video production along with a strong sense of typography, color theory, composition, print, broadcast and digital communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability and willingness to stay on top of current trends, industry knowledge, and develop new skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re confident when providing direction to partners and teams&lt;/li&gt;
