&lt;p&gt;Creative Directors are the architects of the creative vision at SixSpeed. They transform business challenges, consumer insight, and cultural opportunity into original ideas that make brands impossible to imitate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They lead with clarity, conviction, and momentum, keeping teams engaged, aligned, and producing sharp work. They know concept is king but execution is everything, directing campaigns, experiences, and brand assets from the first spark through the final detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creative Directors oversee multiple projects, build trusted client relationships, and push, protect, and sell great work. As leaders and managers, they embody SixSpeed’s culture while advancing their teams’ skills, careers, and craft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TASK AT HAND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the creative vision for integrated campaigns and ideas for a variety of outdoor, retail, and CPG brands in a team-centric environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop creative strategies for marketing, advertising, and branding campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and shape work that is strategically sound and conceptually bold to connect people and brands in ways that are impossible to imitate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster and maintain senior-level relationships with clients acting as a strategic partner by demonstrating a deep understanding of their market, business sector and their specific challenges and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and communicate clients goals, objectives and business landscape to the creative team (in a way that inspires and evokes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire and motivate teams to create their best work; promote the environment for creativity to flourish&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and push the SixSpeed creative process to evolve the agency and spur creative teams to do their best work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, timely, and helpful feedback to improve creative output and processes keeping work on budget and schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Account group to provide guidance, insights, and perspectives in support of client initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that employees are up-to-date and the agency maintains relevancy, on branding, marketing, and advertising trends and technological advances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assign, oversee and monitor copywriter, design, and other creative jobs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate brainstorming sessions with teams to generate ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in establishing schedules for short-term and long-term projects, planning jobs and resources accordingly to ensure goals and deadlines are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the execution of all creative work stays within budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the hiring and managing of freelance and full-time Copywriters, Art Directors, Designers, and other members or contractors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess, review and curate creative work for client presentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present creative work to clients and gather the necessary feedback in order to modify the proposal to obtain their approval&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly manage and mentor team members encouraging their growth and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for SixSpeed through developing thought leadership and industry relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve got 7-15 years of experience in the advertising or marketing industryYou’re Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite including InDesign, Photoshop, Illustrator, and have cursory knowledge of programs like After Effects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a natural, strong sense of typography, color theory, composition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in large-scale campaign work and video produc

&lt;p&gt;At SixSpeed, momentum never really stops — it just shifts gears.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re always on the lookout for curious minds, creative thinkers, and people who bring their full selves to what they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if there’s not an open role that matches your background right now, we still want to know you. If you think you’d be a great fit here, culturally, creatively, or just in spirit — tell us. Drop your info, your work, your story — whatever shows us who you are and what you’re about.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ll keep your name on deck for when the right opportunity hits. Because when it does, we move fast and we’d rather already know you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in collaboration and believe the best ideas come from working together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re curious, adaptable, and never satisfied with “good enough.”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring energy and optimism, even when solving tough problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take ownership, follow through, and deliver — no matter the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re passionate about building impactful work with national brands, and making your mark at an independent Minneapolis agency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re looking for a full-time home to grow your career.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be what others can’t, you have to do what they won&#39;t. We are SixSpeed, a full-service advertising agency that is employee-owned, consumer-centric, and ready to deliver on experience. We&#39;re here to make the world&#39;s most adventurous brands impossible to imitate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a Project Manager at SixSpeed, you’ll be the engine that keeps projects moving forward. You will lead cross-functional teams, manage timelines and budgets, and ensure that every deliverable meets client expectations and agency standards. Working closely with Account and Creative teams, you’ll balance details with the bigger picture to make sure projects are delivered on time, on scope, and on budget. We’re looking for a proactive problem-solver who thrives in a fast-paced environment, communicates clearly, and keeps the work, and the team, on track.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TASK AT HAND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional teams to ensure projects are delivered on time, within scope, and within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with members of the Account Team to understand client objectives, priorities, and expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define project scope and deliverables and develop comprehensive project plans, timelines, and budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate the project plan at kick-off with clearly defined deliverables, team member responsibilities, and project milestones/timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allocate and manage resources effectively, ensuring that the right team members are assigned to each project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor team workloads and redistribute tasks as necessary to maintain optimal productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project budgets throughout the life of the project, proactively and collaboratively monitoring hours and hard costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain project timelines, proactively identifying and mitigating potential roadblocks, solving problems before they turn into larger issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement contingency plans to ensure project success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular updates and reports to internal stakeholders on project status, milestones, and key performance indicators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular reviews to ensure that project deliverables meet or exceed client expectations and agency standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete budget reconciliations and after-action reports, with a focus on continuously improving project outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively portfolio manage client budgets across larger, more comprehensive accounts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive project management experience in the advertising/marketing industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in project management processes and the ability to be dynamic in adopting new technologies and methodologies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional interpersonal and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills, always coming to the table with a solution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in budget management, with a strong grasp of mathematical concepts and the ability to effectively allocate resources to optimize project outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;History of success in leading and delivering multiple complex, integrated projects,&amp;nbsp; concurrently on time and within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be what others can’t, you have to do what they won&#39;t. We are SixSpeed, a full-service advertising agency that is employee-owned, audience-first, and built to deliver big ideas at speed. We&#39;re here to make the world&#39;s most adventurous brands impossible to imitate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
